# Formatting Test
Title: Formatting Test

## Dramatis Personae

NARRATOR - The guide through formatting

## ACT I

### SCENE 1

NARRATOR
This line has *italic* text.

NARRATOR
This line has **bold** text.

NARRATOR
This line has ***bold italic*** text.

NARRATOR
This line has _underline_ text.

NARRATOR
This line has ~strikethrough~ text.

// Formatting spanning multiple words
NARRATOR
She said it was *absolutely incredible* and he agreed.

NARRATOR
The word was **extremely important** to remember.

NARRATOR
It was a ***truly magnificent*** display.

NARRATOR
Please _read the instructions_ carefully.

NARRATOR
The feature is ~no longer supported~ in this version.

// Multiple formats in one line
NARRATOR
He was *nervous*, **determined**, and _resolute_.

// Nested formatting
NARRATOR
She whispered ***the secret _code_ word*** to him.

// Bold inside italic context
NARRATOR
In *this italic phrase with **bold** inside* we test nesting.

// Unclosed formatting (edge case)
NARRATOR
This has an *unclosed italic that runs to end of line

NARRATOR
And this has **unclosed bold that also runs on

NARRATOR
Back to normal text with no formatting issues.
